WEBVTT

00:00.600 --> 00:03.636
                ♪               

00:07.240 --> 00:11.878
          [piano music          
      and ambient chatter]      

00:11.911 --> 00:13.146
     Can I get you another?     

00:13.179 --> 00:15.181
 No, you don't have to do that. 

00:15.215 --> 00:16.716
            I insist.           

00:16.750 --> 00:17.884
           Okay, fine.          

00:17.917 --> 00:19.152
         Gin and tonic.         

00:19.185 --> 00:20.653
        Coming right up.        

00:20.687 --> 00:23.189
         We'll take two         
     gin and tonics, please.    

00:23.223 --> 00:25.759
    So, you come here often?    

00:25.825 --> 00:28.228
             Often?             
          Try... a lot.         

00:28.261 --> 00:30.930
         Why don't I try        
   giving you a call instead?   

00:30.997 --> 00:32.098
              Hmm?              

00:32.165 --> 00:33.933
        Sorry, I thought        
        my phone vibrated       

00:34.000 --> 00:35.869
         but it was just        
       my leg being weird.      

00:35.902 --> 00:38.004
        MAN: I get that.        
    My legs are the weirdest.   

00:38.038 --> 00:41.074
        Why do you think        
  I'm wearing pants right now?  

00:41.107 --> 00:43.009
       WOMAN: I feel like       
   I know you from somewhere.   

00:43.043 --> 00:44.177
        Are you an actor?       

00:44.210 --> 00:47.680
   I don't know, you tell me.   

00:47.714 --> 00:49.549
        -Ring any bells?        
         -I'm not sure.         

00:49.582 --> 00:51.584
     You kind of just rubbed    
    your eyes really hard...?   

00:51.618 --> 00:52.952
     MAN: That was my line.     

00:53.019 --> 00:54.454
    You didn't say anything.    

00:54.521 --> 00:56.556
      -Acting is reacting.      
     -[vigorous ice shaking]    

00:56.589 --> 00:58.691
   WOMAN: Yeah, I guess it is.  

00:58.725 --> 01:01.127
     MAN: So, tell me about     
       yourself, Boo-Boo.       

01:01.194 --> 01:03.396
         Yeah... can you        
      not call me Boo-Boo?      

01:03.430 --> 01:05.231
         Oh, I'm sorry.         
  I thought that was your name. 

01:05.265 --> 01:07.067
      WOMAN: And why would      
        that be my name?        

01:07.100 --> 01:08.768
      MAN: Well, I noticed      
      you have a Band-Aid,      

01:08.802 --> 01:10.270
      which means somebody      
         has a boo-boo!         

01:10.303 --> 01:12.906
     WOMAN: Oh, we're giving    
    each other nicknames now?   

01:12.939 --> 01:15.241
   Well, I notice that you're   
     clearly wearing a wig,     

01:15.275 --> 01:17.243
     so why don't I call you    
         Fucking Weird?         

01:17.277 --> 01:19.446
    MAN: Can't say I haven't    
     heard that one before.     

01:19.479 --> 01:21.414
    I have what Will Smith's    
            wife has.           

01:21.448 --> 01:22.882
      WOMAN: Hmm, alopecia?     

01:22.916 --> 01:24.984
   No, just a badass attitude   
      and my own talk show.     

01:25.051 --> 01:26.419
       -[bartender grunts]      
        -Who's Alopecia?        

01:26.453 --> 01:27.654
   WOMAN: You're really cute.   

01:27.720 --> 01:29.122
          Oh, I thought         
     I was "Fucking Weird."     

01:29.155 --> 01:30.423
        -Nice to meet me!       
           -[giggles]           

01:30.457 --> 01:32.459
          -[loud crash]         
     -Wanna get out of here?    

01:32.492 --> 01:34.661
    I don't think we're ever    
      gonna get our drinks.     

01:34.727 --> 01:37.163
  If a bear shits in the woods, 
      does anybody hear it?     

01:37.230 --> 01:38.565
      I'm in love with you.     

01:38.598 --> 01:41.301
      Let's get outta here.     
  Speeches are about to start.  

01:41.334 --> 01:43.803
                ♪               

01:43.837 --> 01:45.805
                ♪               

01:45.839 --> 01:49.142
            [screams]           

01:49.175 --> 01:52.479
          [theme music]         

01:52.512 --> 01:55.415
                ♪               

01:55.448 --> 01:58.084
  ♪ I'm a different person now ♪

01:58.118 --> 02:00.954
   ♪ Can we just hug it out? ♪  

02:00.987 --> 02:03.823
     ♪ There's an elephant ♪    

02:03.857 --> 02:06.626
    ♪ There's an elephant... ♪  

02:06.659 --> 02:10.997
     ♪ There's an elephant ♪    

02:14.534 --> 02:17.103
      This is a special day     

02:17.137 --> 02:22.275
       for my son and his       
    beautiful new wife, sure,   

02:22.308 --> 02:24.177
        but for us, too.        

02:24.210 --> 02:27.981
         [in a whisper]         
           I love you!          

02:28.014 --> 02:33.219
 As you all know, 17 years ago, 
   my wife and I sat in a room  

02:33.286 --> 02:37.524
    and were told by a doctor   
   that our 11-year-old son...  

02:37.557 --> 02:39.792
 had an incurable brain tumour, 

02:39.826 --> 02:41.861
          and only had          
      a year left to live.      

02:41.895 --> 02:43.363
      DOCTOR: Mm-mm, mm-mm!     

02:43.396 --> 02:46.032
          No, I didn't!         

02:46.065 --> 02:47.033
           Excuse me?           

02:47.066 --> 02:48.134
          No, I didn't!         

02:48.168 --> 02:51.070
    Oh! [chuckles nervously]    
            Dr. Hong!           

02:51.137 --> 02:52.739
        Why is he wearing       
      his doctor's outfit?      

02:52.805 --> 02:54.874
  I did not, nor would I ever,  
          tell a parent         

02:54.908 --> 02:57.143
      that their child had      
    only a year left to live.   

02:57.177 --> 02:59.479
           -Oh, uh...           
   Well, thank you for coming.  

02:59.512 --> 03:00.513
         We hope that--         

03:00.547 --> 03:02.015
  -I simply gave you the facts  

03:02.048 --> 03:03.883
      and stated that only      
  a small percentage of people  

03:03.917 --> 03:06.319
  with the type of brain tumour 
      he had would survive.     

03:06.352 --> 03:08.321
